{
  "texts": [
    "Dataset DescriptionThe dataset used for training and testing the modified Mistral LLM included a blend of diverse text sources and specific tests from Google's BIG-Bench test set, chosen for their relevance to accurate information retrieval and reasoning.",
    "The text sources ensured comprehensive coverage of language nuances:❼ A collection of contemporary English literary works, approximately 1 billion words ❼ Technical and scientific papers, around 500 million words, covering various domains ❼ A corpus of online news articles, totaling 750 million words, to capture current language usage and colloquialisms ❼ Datasets of dialogues and conversational texts, around 300 million words, to enhance the model's conversational abilities Additionally, table 1 lists the following tests from Google's BIG-Bench, integrated to assess the model's performance in key areas:This integration of diverse text sources and targeted BIG-Bench tests provided a robust and multifaceted environment for training and evaluating the Mistral LLM, particularly in the areas of logical reasoning, analytical thinking, and understanding complex language structures.",
    "ResultsThis section presents the results of integrating the Probabilistic Inference Layer (PIL) into the Mistral LLM, compared against the original model.",
    "The performance was evaluated over four tests: Analogical Similarity, Analytic Entailment, Arithmetic, and Boolean Expressions.",
    "Increase in AccuracyThe integration of the Probabilistic Inference Layer (PIL) into the Mistral LLM has resulted in a marked improvement in the model's ability to retrieve factual information accurately."
  ]
}